[
    // Encounter sections (^$land_encounter / ^$surf_encounter_* / ^$fishing_* / ^$headbutting
    // / ^$rocksmash_encounter) deliberately carry NO ^$dark, even in dark areas like Rock
    // Tunnel. It is not missing: their ^$CanReach points at a shared per-table leaf in
    // scripts/logic/regions/encounter_leafs.lua, and that file loads BEFORE
    // connections_darkareas.lua, so gate_region_exits ANDs the Flash gate onto each attach
    // EDGE individually. A ^$dark here would be wrong for the 6 tables that straddle dark and
    // lit regions -- FISHING_Ocean has 1 dark attach point and 23 lit ones, so a section-level
    // gate would demand Flash to fish at Olivine. Change DARK_AREA_REGIONS and every encounter
    // follows automatically; a copy of the gate here would just go stale.
